12-15 November - Summer Squash Casserole

- 2   lb sliced squash (6 cups)
- 1/4 cup chopped onions
- 1   can condensed cream of chicken or mushroom soup
- 1   cup sour cream
- 1   cup shredded carrots
- 8   oz packaged herb seasonal stuffing mix
- 1/2 cup melted butter or margarine

 In a saucepan cook squash and onions in boiling salted water for 5 minutes, drain. Combine cream of chicken or mushroom soup and sour cream. Stir in carrots. Fold in squash and onions. Combine stuffing mix and melted butter. Spread 1/2 stuffing mix in bottom of a 12x9" pan, spoon vegetable mix on top. Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over vegetables. Bake at 350F for 25-30 minutes or until heated through. 